[39:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'few images into a 3D scene, but they struggle to scale up to 4K resolution. Once you push the resolution higher, things get messy, slow, and way too heavy to compute. Now, LGTM is able to'

[39:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'change that by using fewer blocks to represent a scene at a time. Instead of increasing the number of Gaussians as the resolution goes up, it keeps them compact and instead attaches a texture to each one. So, think of it like this.'

[40:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Instead of like placing thousands of tiny colored dots to form an image, you place fewer dots, but each one carries a small patch of detailed texture. And this allows it to generate a full 4K resolution 3D scene without like blowing'

[40:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'up compute. Here are several screenshots from a 3D scene. On the left is without this new LGTM, and on the right is with this new LGTM. And as you can see, the resolution is just a lot better for all'

